  "_comment": "Curated iconic polytonic Ancient Greek surface forms and lemmas that should always receive frequency bucket 'C' (Common) in the Hunspell export, regardless of raw corpus token count. Rationale: highly-inflected classical lemmas (e.g. Homer's verb ἀείδω, Ζεύς, μῆνις) have their corpus mass diluted across hundreds of forms, so no single polytonic surface form crosses the 1000-occurrence threshold - but they are culturally canonical and end users expect autocorrect to strongly prefer them. The monotonic variants are deliberately omitted so that, when a user types a stripped-accent input, the polytonic canonical form outranks the monotonic variant at tiebreak. Forms with grave accent on final vowel (e.g. τὸ vs τό) are sandhi variants that Hunspell and Tonos treat as equally valid; where both are canonically attested we include both.",
